def fetch_processor(text):
    if 'Intel Core i7' in text:
        return 'Intel Core i7'
    elif 'Intel Core i5' in text:
        return 'Intel Core i5'
    elif 'Intel Core i3' in text:
        return 'Intel Core i3'
    elif 'Intel' in text:
        return 'Other Intel Processor'
    else:
        return 'AMD Processor'

df['Cpu brand'] = df['Cpu Name'].apply(fetch_processor)

# creating four new features named 'HDD' 'SSD' 'Hybrid' 'Flash Storage' from 'Memory'
In [96]:
df['Memory'] = df['Memory'].astype(str).str.replace(r'\.0', '', regex=True)
df['Memory'] = df['Memory'].str.replace('GB', '').str.replace('TB', '000')


df[['first', 'second']] = df['Memory'].str.split("+", expand=True, n=1)
df['second'].fillna("0", inplace=True)


df[['first_size', 'first_type']] = df['first'].str.extract(r'(\d+)([A-Za-z ]*)')
df[['second_size', 'second_type']] = df['second'].str.extract(r'(\d+)([A-Za-z ]*)')


df['first_size'] = df['first_size'].astype(float).fillna(0).astype(int)
df['second_size'] = df['second_size'].astype(float).fillna(0).astype(int)


storage_types = ['HDD', 'SSD', 'Hybrid', 'Flash Storage']

for storage in storage_types:
    df[storage] = (
        np.where(df['first_type'].str.contains(storage, na=False), df['first_size'], 0) +
        np.where(df['second_type'].str.contains(storage, na=False), df['second_size'], 0)
    )


df.drop(columns=['Memory', 'first', 'second', 'first_size', 'first_type', 'second_size', 'second_type'], inplace=True)

def cat_os(inp):
    os_dict = {
        'Windows 10': 'Windows',
        'Windows 7': 'Windows',
        'Windows 10 S': 'Windows',
        'macOS': 'Mac',
        'Mac OS X': 'Mac'
    }
    return os_dict.get(inp, 'Others/No OS/Linux')

df['os'] = df['OpSys'].map(cat_os)

# after applying log tranform,skewed data become normal.Also,the impact of outliers reduced.

from scipy.stats import zscore


df['Z_Score_Price'] = np.abs(zscore((df['Price'])))


outliers_z = df[df['Z_Score_Price'] > 3]
print("Outliers detected using Z-Score without log transform:", outliers_z.shape[0])


df['Z_Score_Price'] = np.abs(zscore((np.log(df['Price']))))


outliers_z = df[df['Z_Score_Price'] > 3]
print("Outliers detected using Z-Score with log transform:", outliers_z.shape[0])

Outliers detected using Z-Score without log transform: 12
Outliers detected using Z-Score with log transform: 1

VOTING REGRESSOR

from sklearn.ensemble import VotingRegressor,StackingRegressor

step1 = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[
    ('col_tnf',OneHotEncoder(sparse_output=False,drop='first'),[0,1,7,10,11])],remainder='passthrough')
rf = RandomForestRegressor(max_depth= 20, max_features= 0.5, max_samples= None, n_estimators= 200)
gbdt = GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators=500)
xgb = XGBRegressor(n_estimators=45,max_depth=5,learning_rate=0.5)
step2 = VotingRegressor([('rf', rf), ('gbdt', gbdt), ('xgb',xgb)],weights=[5,1,1])
pipe = Pipeline([
    ('step1',step1),
    ('step2',step2)])
pipe.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred = pipe.predict(X_test)
print('R2 score',r2_score(y_test,y_pred))
print('MAE',mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_pred))

R2 score 0.9751760677740932
MAE 0.05471817593125627

STACKING

In [199]:
step1 = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[
    ('col_tnf',OneHotEncoder(sparse_output=False,drop='first'),[0,1,7,10,11])],remainder='passthrough')
estimators = [
    ('rf', RandomForestRegressor(max_depth= 20, max_features= 0.5, max_samples= None, n_estimators= 200)),
    ('gbdt',GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators=500)),
    ('xgb', XGBRegressor(n_estimators=45,learning_rate=0.5,max_depth=5))]
step2 = StackingRegressor(estimators=estimators, final_estimator=Ridge(alpha=100))
pipe = Pipeline([
    ('step1',step1),
    ('step2',step2)])
pipe.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred = pipe.predict(X_test)
print('R2 score',r2_score(y_test,y_pred))
print('MAE',mean_absolute_error(y_test,y_pred))

R2 score 0.968731488210994
MAE 0.07539300450899523
